  "texts": [
    "patch), to generate an output 11.",
    "By design, these patch-level approaches ignore up to 99% of the total tissue, miss potentially diagnostically relevant areas, and cannot be applied to tasks that require the full context of the entire tissue sample (e.g., tumor thickness prediction).",
    "Slide-level approaches, on the other hand, aggregate information from all patches into a slide-level representation that can be used in downstream tasks, most notably biomarker prediction 9.",
    "A recent direction of research is to extend the capabilities of such methods by incorporating medical text.",
    "Contrastive vision language models in pathology, such as PLIP 12 and CONCH 13, align text and images at the patch-level."
  ]
}